  Step 2 — Identify the Classes (Entities)                                                                                                                                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                              
  Before writing any code, identify what needs to exist:
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  RateLimiter      → the front door. receives (client_id, endpoint),
                     looks up which algorithm to use, delegates to it                                                                                                                                           
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  Limiter          → abstract contract (interface) that ALL algorithms                                                                                                                                          
                     must follow. One method: allow(key)                                                                                                                                                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  TokenBucketLimiter    → implements Limiter using token bucket algorithm                                                                                                                                       
  SlidingWindowLimiter  → implements Limiter using sliding window log algorithm                                                                                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  LimiterFactory   → given raw config dict, creates the right Limiter object                                                                                                                                    
  
  RateLimitResult  → structured return value (allowed, remaining, retry_after_ms)                                                                                                                               
                                                                                                                                                                                                              
  Why not just one big class?                                                                                                                                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                                                                              
  # BAD — everything in one class                                                                                                                                                                               
  class RateLimiter:                                                                                                                                                                                          
      def allow(self, client_id, endpoint):
          config = self.configs[endpoint]                                                                                                                                                                       
          if config["algorithm"] == "TokenBucket":
              # token bucket logic here                                                                                                                                                                         
          elif config["algorithm"] == "SlidingWindowLog":                                                                                                                                                       
              # sliding window logic here
          # adding new algorithm = modify this class = risky                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  # GOOD — each algorithm is its own class                                                                                                                                                                      
  # Adding new algorithm = add new class, touch nothing else                                                                                                                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  This is the Open/Closed Principle — open for extension, closed for modification.                                                                                                                              
  
